msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk_01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Good grief... I can't believe the <2.se_co>chief's\n"
"heirloom<3.re_co> was stolen by thieves..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk_02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh, the helmet that was supposed to be\n"
"Lady Urbosa's favorite, right?\n"
"\n"
"It's been handed down from chief to\n"
"chief for generations. Apparently the\n"
"<2.se_co>chief<3.re_co> is pretty distressed."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hey, have you heard? Apparently the\n"
"chief's heirloom has been returned!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_04"
msgid "<1.so>She's still so small, too... Poor thing..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_05"
msgid ""
"<1.so>They have an idea of who committed the\n"
"theft, but the thieves aren't amateurs...\n"
"I heard they're professional assassins."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_06"
msgid ""
"<1.so>That explains why the barracks have\n"
"been noisier than usual."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk_07"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I heard, I heard!<2.pa>\n"
"Something about an amazing Hylian\n"
"vai, right?\n"
"That's got to take a lot of weight off\n"
"the <3.se_co>chief<4.re_co>'s shoulders, huh?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_08"
msgid ""
"<1.so>But there's still a chance that the thieves\n"
"will come back here, so we've got to\n"
"keep vigilant for a while, right?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_09"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Speaking of which, the Divine Beast\n"
"has gotten quiet, huh?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_10"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Now that you mention it, I haven't\n"
"noticed any rocking or shaking at all..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_11"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I wonder if this has something to do with\n"
"the chief's heirloom being returned..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "Talk_12"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You definitely don't look old\n"
"enough to drink here yet...\n"
"How old are you, really?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: pause (longer)
#. 4: sound
#. 5: pause (longer)
msgctxt "Talk_13"
msgid ""
"<1.so>...<2.pa><3.pa>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<4.so>AH HA HA!<5.pa>\n"
"What a funny vai you are! When you're\n"
"older, let's have a drink together!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_14"
msgid "<1.so>These drinks are for adults, got it?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk_15"
msgid ""
"<1.so>The desert gets pretty cold at night,\n"
"you know...\n"
"\n"
"You'll be fine dressed like that in town,\n"
"but if you go outside the walls, you'll\n"
"catch a cold or worse, for sure!\n"
"If you don't have a <2.se_co>warm doublet<3.re_co>, you'd\n"
"better rest at a hotel until morning."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "Talk_16"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh? Who are you again?<2.pa> I might well\n"
"know you, but then again... Maybe not!\n"
"\n"
"I've had fun drinking today, too!\n"
"I've got to do this again tomorrow!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: text_size
msgctxt "Talk_17"
msgid "<1.so><2.te_si>Urk...I don't feel so good...<3.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "Talk_18"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Sorry, but can you please keep it down?<2.pa>\n"
"I've got an awful headache..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_19"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Nali and I chat every day, but we never\n"
"tire of talking about the same things.\n"
"\n"
"When I'm with my vai friends, I feel like\n"
"we could talk forever."
msgstr ""

